HEADWORD: Semifloscule
<hw>Sem"i*flos`cule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A floscule, or florest, with its corolla prolonged into a
strap-shaped petal; -- called also
<altname>semifloret</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semiflosculous</ent>⟦br⟧
